			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Windows Breakpad registers a handler using SetUnhandledExceptionFilter() to catch crashes.  But this handler will not get called if the process has a debugger attached, which is how we're implementing hardware exception handling.

&amp;quot;After calling this function, *if an exception occurs in a process that is not being debugged*, and the exception makes it to the unhandled exception filter, that filter will call the exception filter function specified by the lpTopLevelExceptionFilter parameter.&amp;quot;
- http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms680634(v=vs.85).aspx

We'll need to fix this.
